The following property acquired by the couple during the marriage is the joint property of the couple and is jointly owned by the couple: 
(i) wages, bonuses, remuneration for labour; 
(ii) proceeds of production, management, investment; 
(iii) proceeds of intellectual property; 
(iv) inheritance or gifted property, except as provided for in article 163, paragraph 3, of this Law; 
(v) other property which shall be jointly owned. 


 husband and wife have equal rights to dispose of the joint property.

