The following matters shall be decided by the owner jointly: 

(i) establish and amend the rules of procedure of the proprietor; 

(ii) establish and amend the management statute; 

(iii) elect or replace the owner committee; 

(iv) select and dismiss the property service enterprise or other administrator; 

(v) use the funds for the maintenance of the building and its ancillary facilities; 

(vi) raise funds for the maintenance of the building and its ancillary facilities; 

(vii) alter, reconstruct the building and its ancillary facilities; 

(viii) change the use of the common or use the shared part of the owner committee; 

(ix) decide other important matters relating to shared and common management rights. 

(ix) jointly decide matters shall be voted upon by a majority of owners with more than two thirds of the total and more than two thirds of the total number of owners.

